Finally, in the last days of October, Merkel has come out again with a clear position, calling for a reform of the European Union's agreements in order to enable a country to be saved, while at the same time requiring private lenders to bear part of the costs.
This position was interpreted as anti-European, as it fueled the Irish crisis and all the following.
